{
  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "markdown-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": "# Reading Mode Demo\n\nThis notebook demonstrates the **Reading Mode** feature, which hides all editing UI elements and shows only the content and outputs.\n\nIn reading mode:\n- ✅ Inputs remain interactive (reactive values)\n- ✅ Outputs are displayed and updated\n- ❌ No editing controls or cell separators\n- ❌ No hover effects or cell selection"
    },
    {
      "id": "input-price",
      "type": "input",
      "variableName": "basePrice",
      "value": 100,
      "inputType": "number",
      "label": "Base Price ($)",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1000
    },
    {
      "id": "input-tax",
      "type": "input",
      "variableName": "taxRate",
      "value": 0.08,
      "inputType": "number",
      "label": "Tax Rate",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "step": 0.01
    },
    {
      "id": "formula-total",
      "type": "formula",
      "variableName": "totalPrice",
      "formula": "basePrice * (1 + taxRate)"
    },
    {
      "id": "code-calculation",
      "type": "code",
      "code": "// Calculate pricing breakdown\nconst breakdown = {\n  basePrice: basePrice,\n  taxAmount: basePrice * taxRate,\n  totalPrice: totalPrice,\n  savings: basePrice > 500 ? basePrice * 0.05 : 0\n};\n\noutput(breakdown);\n\n// Export for other cells\nexports.breakdown = breakdown;"
    },
    {
      "id": "markdown-summary",
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": "## Summary\n\nBase Price: **${{basePrice}}**  \nTax Rate: **{{taxRate * 100}}%**  \nTotal Price: **${{totalPrice.toFixed(2)}}**\n\n> Try changing the input values above to see the reactive updates!"
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Reading Mode Test",
    "description": "Test notebook for reading mode functionality"
  }
}
